"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780335","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-13","<p>Whilst the Government recognises the Turkish Cypriot community, we do not recognise the self-declared &quot;Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus&quot;. The Government is bound by relevant UN Security Council Resolutions condemning the Turkish Cypriot unilateral declaration of independence from the Republic of Cyprus. In a recent interview the British High Commissioner to Cyprus commented on how best to create conditions of security for the inhabitants of Cyprus, including the Turkish Cypriots. As he said, the Government continues to believe that a just and lasting settlement in Cyprus is the best means of resolving the difficulties caused by partition of the island for all its inhabitants, including matters relating to security. The High Commissioner enjoys the full and total confidence of Ministers.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-11-13T17:43:11.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780335/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780335/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-30","Northern Cyprus: Recognition of States","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether Matthew Kidd, the British High Commissioner to the Republic of Cyprus, was acting on ministerial instructions when he publicly stated that recognition of the TRNC would be “dangerous”; whether they have repudiated recognition of the identity of Turkish Cypriots; and whether they intend to take any action, including disciplinary action.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL2699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780336","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-13","<p>The consultation <em>Financing Growth in Innovative Firms </em>set out the vital role the Enterprise Investment Scheme (EIS) plays in incentivising investment into early stage, high-growth firms. In 2015-16 more than 3,400 companies raised £1.9 billion through the scheme. The consultation also noted an ongoing issue of low-risk ‘capital preservation’ investments structured around the relief and asked an open question about how best to target the relief to ensure it helps innovative, high-growth firms receive the investment they need. The government will set out its response to the consultation in the Budget.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-11-13T15:48:54.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780336/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780336/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-30","Enterprise Investment Scheme","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have for revising the Enterprise Investment Scheme; and what assessment they have made of the economic impact of any future reductions in support available through that scheme.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL2700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780337","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-10","<p>Both the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and the Department for International Trade have staff working in a wide range of policy development and delivery activities which support small businesses across the UK. The information is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2017-11-10T12:50:39.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780337/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780337/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-30","Small Businesses","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many civil servants in (1) the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, and (2) the Department for International Trade, were responsible for small business policy in each year since 2010, broken down by grade.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL2701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780338","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-10","<p>The Small Business Commissioner’s complaints handling service, dependent on secondary legislation, is expected to be launched by the end of the year, subject to the will of Parliament. The service will be supported by an advice website which is also planned to launch at the same time and will provide details on how complaints from small businesses will be dealt with.</p><p> </p><p>The Commissioner, Paul Uppal, and his team are in the process of setting up the office and engaging across the business community and with stakeholders to raise awareness of the SBC service.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2017-11-10T12:38:41.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780338/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780338/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-30","Small Business Commissioner","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Prior of Brampton on 19 October (HL1856), how long after the planned launch date of 1 October they expect the Small Business Commissioner complaints scheme to launch; and what marketing activity they are carrying out to ensure that small businesses are aware that complaints dating back to April 2017 may be made retrospectively, once the service has launched.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL2702"
