"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780391","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>Ministers hold regular meetings with a wide range of stakeholders, including from the alcohol industry.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-11-06T15:11:30.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780391/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780391/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-30","Whisky: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Scotch Whisky Association on tax on whisky.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780392","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>This information is not available as the government does not break down the amount of duty collected from spirits by Scotch Whisky.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the amount of duty collected through alcohol taxation is routinely published online by HM Revenue &amp; Customs in the ‘Tax &amp; Duty Bulletins’ section of the UK Trade Info website. This can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx</a></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","110443","2017-11-06T12:03:22.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780392/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780392/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-30","Whisky: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much excise duty was collected on Scotch whisky in the past five financial years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780393","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-06","<p>This information is not available as the government does not break down the amount of duty collected from spirits by Scotch Whisky.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the amount of duty collected through alcohol taxation is routinely published online by HM Revenue &amp; Customs in the ‘Tax &amp; Duty Bulletins’ section of the UK Trade Info website. This can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/Pages/TaxAndDutybulletins.aspx</a></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","110442","2017-11-06T12:03:22.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780393/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780393/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-30","Whisky: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of any increase in excise duty collected from the sale of Scotch whisky in the current financial year.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110443"
