"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780425","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Secretary of State is required by law to complete a review of the Single Source Contract Regulations within three years of them coming into force. He will announce the results of the review, including any proposed changes to legislation, in due course.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:40:16.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780425/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780425/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the NAO Report, Improving value for money in non-competitive procurement of defence equipment, published on 25 October 2017, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Single Source Contract Regulations under the Defence Reform Act 2014.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780426","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer I gave on 16 October 2017 to Question 106955 to the hon. Member for Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport (Luke Pollard).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T17:29:21.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780426/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780426/answer","20171016_106955_WQnA_extract_on_Warships_Decommissioning.docx","20171016_106955_WQnA_extract_on_Warships_Decommissioning.docx","106955 - Warships Decommissioning","106955 - Warships Decommissioning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780426/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the future is of HMS Ocean and HMS Bulwark; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Drax","South Dorset","Richard Drax","110276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780427","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-03","<p>The data for Ministry of Defence (MOD) redundancy payments to civilian employees alone is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD’s combined expenditure for civilian redundancy and early retirement for the last three financial years is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015-16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Civilian Redundancy and Early Retirement expenditure (£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p>£87.781</p></td><td><p>£33.822</p></td><td><p>£18.290</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-03T14:01:15.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780427/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780427/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on redundancy payments to civilian employees in each of the past three years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780428","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>As an executive, non-departmental public body, the Single Source Regulations Office (SSRO) is set up such that the day to-day decisions are independent and are removed from Ministers and Civil Servants. Ministry of Defence Ministers are, however, ultimately responsible to Parliament for its independence, effectiveness and efficiency.</p><p>We have no plans to change this.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:38:05.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780428/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780428/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Single Source Regulations Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will break his Department's link with the Single Source Regulations Office and make it an independent body.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110196"
