 information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780434/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Armed Forces: Alcoholic Drinks and Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what alcohol and drug testing is currently carried out on military personnel on active service.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","110303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780435","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>The information requested is not held in the format requested. Savings resulting from restructuring are reallocated within the Defence budgeting process. It is not possible to attribute savings to individual posts.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:37:34.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780435/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780435/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the annual savings to the public purse for MOD civilian employees who have (a) accepted redundancy and (b) left the service but whose jobs will not be replaced in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780436","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) has no such plans. The MOD works closely with other Government Departments, Local Authorities, employers and Service charities to ensure that veterans have the support they need, now and in the future.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:40:59.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780436/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780436/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will introduce new veterans support services staffed and run by former service personnel.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","110333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780437","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>The names for the new City Class Type 26 Frigates have been decided and will be announced at appropriate opportunities in the future. So far two ships have been named as HMS GLASGOW and HMS BELFAST.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:39:43.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780437/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780437/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will name one of the new Royal Navy Frigates, HMS Seaham.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","110334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780438","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Naval Service already has a zero tolerance approach regarding the use of any illegal substances, and all personnel are subject to random compulsory drug testing. This policy of no tolerance is reiterated during the recruitment process and throughout the training and career of all Naval Service personnel.</p><p>All Naval Service personnel are mandated to attend the Substance Misuse presentation during New Entry training and thereafter at yearly intervals. Once personnel reach the age of 30, this presentation is delivered at three yearly intervals. They also receive updates during Divisional meetings which are held at least three times a year.</p><p>Additionally, a Management of Alcohol and Substance Misuse presentation is delivered to all Leadership courses in order to increase the awareness and education of our future managers and leaders.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-11-02T16:25:08.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780438/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780438/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Navy: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will review guidelines on the recruitment and training of naval officers in light of positive drug tests aboard HMS Vigilant.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780440","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-07","<p>We are currently considering a range of capability requirements based on the role of the Type 31e, their operating environment and likely future threats that will be faced. Final decisions on Type 31e capabilities will be made closer to the Main Investment Decision point.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-07T17:41:53.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780440/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780440/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Type 31 Frigates: Antisubmarine Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what anti-submarine warfare capability he plans to include on the Type 31e General Purpose Frigate; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","110430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780441","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Ministry of Defence and the Naval Service have a very robust anti-drugs policy and will not tolerate the misuse of drugs by Service personnel. The nine members of HMS VIGILANT's ship's company who tested positive for illegal drugs have been discharged from the Naval Service.</p><p>In addition, the Royal Navy is to conduct increased Compulsory Drug Testing of the Submarine Flotilla.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-02T16:24:17.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780441/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780441/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Navy: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to deal with reports of HMS Vigilant crew members testing positive for class A drugs.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780442","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>All Service personnel are expected to be fit to perform their normal professional duties at all times, including any specific safety critical duties.</p><p>Duty personnel are not permitted to drink while on duty and there are stringent guidelines on the amounts of alcohol that personnel can consume in the 24 hours preceding their duty. These are that no more than five units of alcohol are to be consumed within the 24 hours prior to assuming a duty, with no alcohol to be consumed in the 10 hours prior to assuming a duty.</p><p>Additionally, the Armed Forces Act 2011 has provided the Statutory Instruction to permit alcohol testing of Service personnel, using Home Office approved breathalysers, who are carrying out or are due to carry out any safety critical duties as defined by the Act where 'reasonable cause' exists.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-02T16:10:02.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780442/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780442/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-30","Navy: Drunkenness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps were taken on on-duty consumption of alcohol by naval officers following the fatal shooting of a crew member aboard HMS Astute in 2011.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","110459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780443","Department for Education","false","2017-11-06","<p>An estimate of the cost per digital transaction of applications for full-time study support in October 2018 is not available.</p><p>The most recent data available covers the operational period from 1 January 2016 to 31 December 2016 and shows a cost per digital transaction for applications for full time students of £44.29.</p><p>This information is publicly available via the dataset which can be accessed at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/performance/student-finance-england-full-time-study-applications/cost-per-transaction" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/performance/student-finance-england-full-time-study-applications/cost-per-transaction</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-11-06T13:56:35.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780443/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780443/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Students: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the cost per digital transaction of applications for full-time study support in October 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780444","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The department will carry out an independent evaluation of 30 hours’ free childcare during the first two terms of national rollout.</p><p> </p><p>We currently have an invitation to tender issued which will close on Thursday 2 November. We will review the bids and appoint an independent contractor to undertake the year one evaluation of 30 hours before the end of the year.</p><p> </p><p>Following a scoping exercise the planned timetable for publication of the evaluation will be:</p><ul><li>Research fieldwork: January – May 2018.</li><li>Report publication: by 1 September 2018.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-07T16:38:54.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780444/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780444/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 30 October 2017 to Question 109339, on children: day care, what the timetable is for publication of the independent evaluation.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","110302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780445","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Adoption Leadership Board (ALB) quarterly survey shows the number of children who were part of a sibling group who were adopted from care in England from 2013-14. The reports are published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/adoption-system-performance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/adoption-system-performance</a>.</p><p>Table 1: The number of children who were part of a sibling group who were adopted, in England</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Number of children who were part of a sibling group who were adopted, in England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>1,870</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>1,930</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>1,710</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: ALB quarterly survey</em></p><p>The latest quarterly data shows that there were 870 children who were part of a sibling group who were adopted in the first two quarters of 2016-17.</p><p>We do not hold information prior to 2013-14, or on the actual number of sibling groups.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:14:18.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780445/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780445/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many sibling groups have been adopted in each of the last 10 years.","true","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446","Department for Education","true","2017-11-02","<p>This is a matter for Ofsted. I have asked Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, Amanda Spielman, to write to my hon. Friend the Member for East Worthing and Shoreham (Tim Loughton) with the information requested.<ins class="ministerial"> A copy of the letter will be placed in the Libraries of both Houses.</ins></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:03:59.13Z","2018-01-19T09:15:36.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446/answer","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446/answer/previousversion/19649","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780446/answer/previousversion/19649",,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Foster Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many registered foster carers there have been in each of the last 10 years.","true","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780447","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Adoption Leadership Board (ALB) quarterly survey shows the number of approvals of adoptive families by local councils and voluntary adoption agencies in England from quarter 4 2013-14. The reports are published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/adoption-system-performance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/adoption-system-performance</a>.</p><p>Table 1: The number of adoptive families who were approved for adoption, in England</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Number of adoptive families who were approved for adoption, in England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Q4 2013-14</p></td><td><p>1,390</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>5,260</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>3,610</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source: ALB quarterly survey</em></p><p>The latest quarterly data shows that there were 1,410 adoptive families approved in the first two quarters of 2016-17.</p><p>This refers to adoptive families rather than people as these are the groups of people available to adopt a child. We do not hold information prior to quarter 4 2013-14.</p><p>Figures for the number of approved adoptive families at 31 March 2013 and 2014 can be found in the Ofsted adoption publications here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/childrens-social-care-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/childrens-social-care-statistics</a>.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:01:42.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780447/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780447/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people have been approved as adopters in each of the last 10 years.","true","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780448","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The number of children who were placed for adoption on 31 March in each of the last 10 years is shown in the table which can be accessed from the link below.</p><p>Figures are published in table A2 of the statistical release <em>Children looked after in England including adoption: 2016 to 2017 </em>at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:26:00.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780448/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780448/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children have been placed for adoption in each of the last 10 years.","true","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780449","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>I am sorry, but the department does not collect data on adoption breakdowns.</p><p>Information on children who started to be looked after and previously had permanent arrangement was collected for the first time in 2014. These figures are published in table C1 of the statistical release <em>Children looked after in England including adoption: 2016 to 2017 </em>at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p><em>Beyond the Adoption Order</em> published in 2014, found that over a 12-year period the national adoption disruption rate was 3.2%, indicating that 3 in 100 adoptions was disrupted over a 12-year period.<strong><br> </strong></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:31:22.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780449/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780449/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many adoptions have broken down in each of the last 10 years.","true","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","110269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780450","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>My Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State has had no correspondence with Suffolk County Council on the 30 hours free childcare policy in the past six months.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:53:58.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780450/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780450/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will publish all correspondence on the 30 hours free childcare policy which she has had with Suffolk Country Council in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","110318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780451","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>All pupils whose parents are in receipt of universal credit (UC) are currently entitled to free school meals (FSM). This is an interim arrangement during the initial roll-out of UC. All pupils registered for FSM attract pupil premium.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education is working closely with the Department for Work and Pensions, other Government departments and other interested parties to establish criteria for determining entitlement to benefits-related FSM as the roll-out progresses. No decision has been taken yet, and our proposals on this matter will be announced in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","110323","2017-11-02T17:33:17.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780451/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780451/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Pupil Premium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which pupils whose parents claim universal credit count towards a school's pupil premium; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780452","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>All pupils whose parents are in receipt of universal credit (UC) are currently entitled to free school meals (FSM). This is an interim arrangement during the initial roll-out of UC. All pupils registered for FSM attract pupil premium.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education is working closely with the Department for Work and Pensions, other Government departments and other interested parties to establish criteria for determining entitlement to benefits-related FSM as the roll-out progresses. No decision has been taken yet, and our proposals on this matter will be announced in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","110321","2017-11-02T17:33:17.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780452/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780452/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which categories claimants of universal credit are entitled to claim free school meals for their children; and whether she plans to review that entitlement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","110323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780453","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The purpose of the Northern Fund, which was announced in December 2014, was to support the expansion of effective academy chains to drive up educational standards across the North (the North, Lancashire and West Yorkshire, and East Midlands and Humber). In 2015, £527,464 was awarded to Wakefield City Academies Trust through this fund to enable the Trust to expand into the Bradford region.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:51:24.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780453/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780453/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, on what the £530,000 from her Department given to Wakefield City Academy Trust as part of the Northern Powerhouse project in 2015 has been spent.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780454","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The department will carry out an independent evaluation of 30 hours’ free childcare during the first two terms of national rollout.</p><p> </p><p>We currently have an invitation to tender issued which will close on Thursday 2 November. We will review the bids and appoint an independent contractor to undertake the year one evaluation of 30 hours before the end of the year.</p><p> </p><p>Following a scoping exercise the planned timetable for publication of the evaluation will be:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Research fieldwork: January – May 2018</li><li>Report publication: by 1 September 2018.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:37:37.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780454/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780454/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 30 October 2017 to Question 109339, on children: day care, what the timetable is for publication of the independent evaluation.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","110384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780455","Department for Education","false","2017-11-02","<p>The funding was allocated to over 350 projects in 123 local authorities (LA) in January 2017 and March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The successful projects by LA were published here - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/early-years-capital-fund-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/early-years-capital-fund-2017</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-02T17:39:11.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780455/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780455/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 30 October 2017 to Question 109407, on children: day care, which local authorities received funding; and how many projects were awarded that funding.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","110361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780456","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The Ministers’ Quarterly Returns release refers to Minister Gibb’s trip to Singapore and Australia. The tickets are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Depart</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Arrive</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Ticket Class</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London Heathrow</p></td><td><p>Singapore Changi International</p></td><td><p>Business</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Singapore Changi International</p></td><td><p>Sydney Kingsford Smith</p></td><td><p>Business</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sydney Kingsford Smith</p></td><td><p>Adelaide</p></td><td><p>Business</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Adelaide</p></td><td><p>Doha Hamad International</p></td><td><p>Business</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Doha Hamad International</p></td><td><p>Manchester</p></td><td><p>Business</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-07T17:38:21.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780456/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780456/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Department for Education: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which tickets relating to which journeys set out in her Department's transparency release entitled Ministers' Quarterly Returns Apr to June 2017, were (a) first, (b) business, (c) economy or (d) any other class.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","110172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780458","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The government knows how important it is that all children with medical conditions are supported to enjoy a full education. That is why we introduced the duty, under section 100 of the Children and Families Act 2014, to require governing bodies to make arrangements to support pupils with medical conditions and have provided statutory guidance outlining schools’ responsibilities in this area.</p><p> </p><p>In complying with this duty, governing bodies should ensure that their school develops a policy for supporting pupils with medical conditions that is reviewed regularly and is readily accessible to parents and school staff.</p><p> </p><p>A school’s ability to support a child for with a medical condition will depend to an appreciable extent on collaborative working between school staff, parents and pupils, and other agencies such as local councils and healthcare professionals.</p><p> </p><p>The school’s policy should therefore identify collaborative working arrangements between all those involved, to help ensure that the needs of pupils with medical conditions are met effectively.</p><p> </p><p>Ofsted’s Common Inspection Framework requires inspectors, in making judgements, to pay particular attention to the outcomes of a range of groups of pupils, including those with medical needs. We also continue to work with organisations such as the Health Conditions in Schools Alliance to help raise further awareness of the duty, and have recently promoted the duty through the department’s social media channels.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","110177 ; 110178 ; 110186","2017-11-07T17:36:54.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780458/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/780458/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-30","Pupils: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to her Department's guidance, entitled Supporting pupils at school with medical conditions, published in December 2015, if she will make an assessment of the proportion of schools with published policies for supporting pupils with medical conditions.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","110185"
